olive oil
1 bag coriander
1 tin sweetcorn
1 carrot
1 packet beef mince
1 packet tomato paste
1 tin black beans
1 packet Plant-Based Mayo
1 bag Shredded Cabbage Mix
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
6 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet Mild Chipotle Sauce
1 tsp brown sugar
1 Brown Onion
1 sachet Tex-Mex spice blend

• Finely chop onion. Grate the carrot. Drain the sweetcorn. Drain and rinse half the black beans.
• Heat a large frying pan over high heat. Cook sweetcorn until lightly browned, 4-5 minutes. Transfer to a large bowl.

TIP: Cover pan with a lid if the corn kernels are “popping” out.

• Return the frying pan to medium heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook onion until tender, 3-4 minutes.
• Add beef mince and cook, breaking up with a spoon, until browned, 4-5 minutes.
• Add garlic paste, Tex-Mex spice blend and tomato paste and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• SPICY! The chipotle sauce is mild, but use less if you're sensitive to heat. Add black beans, mild chipotle sauce, the brown sugar and a splash of water and cook until slightly thickened, 2-3 minutes.
• Remove the pan from heat.

• Add shredded cabbage mix to the charred corn, along with carrot, plant-based mayo and a drizzle of white wine vinegar. Toss to combine and season to taste.
• Microwave mini flour tortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until warmed through.

• Fill each tortilla with some charred corn slaw and chipotle black beans and beef.
• Tear over coriander to serve. Enjoy!